# Go Services Rules

## Project Layout
- cmd/{app}/main.go — entrypoints, minimal code
- internal/{app}/ — application-specific packages (not importable externally)
- pkg/ — shared packages importable by other projects

## Routing & HTTP
- Chi v5 router for HTTP routing
- Middleware chain: logging -> recovery -> cors -> auth
- Handler functions: func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request)
- Use chi.URLParam(r, "paramName") for path parameters

## Error Handling
- Return errors, never panic (except unrecoverable init failures)
- Wrap errors with context: fmt.Errorf("operation: %w", err)
- HTTP handlers write error responses with appropriate status codes
- Use errors.Is/As for error checking

## Logging
- slog for all structured logging
- Include request_id, user_id in log context via middleware
- Log at appropriate levels: Debug for dev, Info for operations, Error for failures

## Context
- context.Context as first parameter for all functions doing I/O
- Propagate context through the call chain
- Use context for cancellation and timeouts
- Store request-scoped values via middleware

## Testing
- Table-driven tests with t.Run("case name", func(t *testing.T) {...})
- Use testify/assert for assertions (not require in subtests)
- httptest.NewServer for integration tests
- t.Parallel() where safe
- Benchmarks for performance-critical code

## Dependencies
- Chi 5.x for routing
- pgx 5.x for PostgreSQL
- go-redis 9.x for Redis
- Cobra 1.9.x + Viper 1.19.x for CLI
